abstract: Consumer confidence has rebounded since recession warnings in the summer, particularly among voters who don’t lean toward either major party.
snippet: Consumer confidence has rebounded since recession warnings in the summer, particularly among voters who don’t lean toward either major party.
lead_paragraph: Americans are feeling better about the economy, a trend that, if it continues, could bolster President Trump’s prospects for re-election in November.

abstract: Former Vice President Joe Biden reported Friday that he had $9 million in reserve at the end of 2019, an underwhelming sum that suggests he could struggle to compete with his better funded rivals in the weeks ahead.
snippet: Former Vice President Joe Biden reported Friday that he had $9 million in reserve at the end of 2019, an underwhelming sum that suggests he could struggle to compete with his better funded rivals in the weeks ahead.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Former Vice President Joe Biden reported Friday that he had $9 million in reserve at the end of 2019, an underwhelming sum that suggests he could struggle to compete with his better funded rivals in the weeks ahead.
headline_main: Biden Cash Reserves Lag Behind Top 2020 Rivals
headline_print_headline: Biden Cash Reserves Lag Behind Top 2020 Rivals

abstract: On a July 25 telephone call with the president of Ukraine, President Trump described Ambassador Yovanovitch as “bad news” and said, ominously, “She’s going to go through some things.”
snippet: On a July 25 telephone call with the president of Ukraine, President Trump described Ambassador Yovanovitch as “bad news” and said, ominously, “She’s going to go through some things.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The American ambassador whose abrupt recall from Ukraine helped lead to President Trump’s impeachment has retired from the State Department, a person familiar with her plans confirmed on Friday.

abstract: Three days before the Iowa caucuses begin the 2020 nominating process, Joe Biden’s campaign manager downplayed the significance of Iowa and New Hampshire and prepped supporters for an extended primary season.
snippet: Three days before the Iowa caucuses begin the 2020 nominating process, Joe Biden’s campaign manager downplayed the significance of Iowa and New Hampshire and prepped supporters for an extended primary season.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Three days before the Iowa caucuses begin the 2020 nominating process, Joe Biden’s campaign manager downplayed the significance of Iowa and New Hampshire and prepped supporters for an extended primary season.
headline_main: Biden Camp Prepping Backers for Extended Fight Beyond Iowa
headline_print_headline: Biden Camp Prepping Backers for Extended Fight Beyond Iowa

abstract: As he discussed the possibility of a White House meeting for Ukraine’s president, President Trump’s lawyer asked to save the Kyiv mayor’s job.
snippet: As he discussed the possibility of a White House meeting for Ukraine’s president, President Trump’s lawyer asked to save the Kyiv mayor’s job.
lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — When Rudolph W. Giuliani met with a top aide to Ukraine’s president last summer, he discussed the prospect of a coveted White House meeting for the president while seeking Ukraine’s commitment to certain investigations that could benefit President Trump politically.

abstract: Amy Klobuchar has often spoken about her prosecution of the teenager in an 11-year-old girl’s murder. This week, an Associated Press report pointed to flaws in the case.
snippet: Amy Klobuchar has often spoken about her prosecution of the teenager in an 11-year-old girl’s murder. This week, an Associated Press report pointed to flaws in the case.
lead_paragraph: Civil rights activists and black community leaders in Minneapolis have called on Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota to suspend her presidential campaign after a report raised questions about whether a black teenager was wrongly convicted of murder during her tenure as the Hennepin County attorney.
